Purpose
The Support Layer is the set of systems mounted around the RAMA Hub that provide power, thermal control, communications, and operational stability.
It is the infrastructure that keeps the factories running, the MOEs working, and the entire hub alive.

The Support Layer is modular, replaceable, and designed to grow as RAMA expands.

Core Functions
The Support Layer provides four essential services:

1. Power Generation
Large solar array wings mounted around the hub

High‑efficiency panels optimized for orbital sunlight

Modular sections that can be replaced or expanded

Direct DC bus feeding factories, MOEs, and comms

2. Thermal Management
Radiator panels mounted on the shadow side of the hub

Passive and active heat rejection

Keeps factories and electronics within safe operating ranges

Designed to scale with factory heat loads

3. Communications & Control
High‑gain antennas for Earth link

Local mesh network for MOEs and factory coordination

Redundant low‑gain antennas for failsafe telemetry

Simple, robust, no‑nonsense comms architecture

4. Structural & Operational Stability
Mounting points for:

Mirror arrays

Additional solar wings

Sensor packages

Future modules

Provides the backbone for all non‑factory systems

Design Philosophy
Modular: Every subsystem can be swapped without redesigning the hub

Redundant: No single failure can shut down RAMA

Simple: Uses proven orbital hardware and standard interfaces

Expandable: As RAMA grows, the Support Layer grows with it

Serviceable: MOEs can replace panels, radiators, and antennas easily

Layout
The Support Layer is arranged around the outer rim of the hub:

Solar arrays on sun‑facing arcs

Radiators on shadow‑facing arcs

Antennas placed for full‑sky coverage

Mirror arrays mounted on adjustable booms

Sensor clusters distributed evenly for situational awareness

This keeps the hub balanced, cool, powered, and connected.

Why This Matters
The Support Layer:

Powers the factories

Keeps the hub thermally stable

Provides communications for MOEs and Earth operators

Enables continuous, autonomous orbital operations

Forms the backbone of RAMA’s long‑term growth

Without the Support Layer, RAMA is just a ring.
With it, RAMA becomes a functioning orbital industrial platform.
